792,0.094253,0.1095,0.11567,0.10904,0.10519,0.094344,0.094766,0.07208,0.055133,0.045388]},{"section":6,"text":"Common causes of such masses include tumors like craniopharyngiomas, which are often associated with calcifications.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034642,0.062278,0.078146,0.090934,0.099925,0.10301,0.10914,0.10635,0.097583,0.085851,0.072077,0.060073],"unified_progress":[0.031311,0.060042,0.081202,0.096809,0.10216,0.12497,0.10817,0.10047,0.094664,0.083451,0.066005,0.050753]},{"section":7,"text":"Craniopharyngiomas are typically benign but can cause significant issues because of their location near critical structures like the optic nerves and the hypothalamus.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034591,0.05892,0.075006,0.087319,0.097195,0.10134,0.10776,0.10569,0.099808,0.089049,0.077584,0.065736],"unified_progress":[0.033768,0.063169,0.082993,0.096429,0.10404,0.10877,0.10566,0.10027,0.098347,0.084281,0.068276,0.053999]},{"section":8,"text":"The symptoms here\u2014headache, visual field defects, and decreased visual acuity\u2014align with what you'd expect from a tumor pressing on the optic chiasm or other nearby areas.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043946,0.06572,0.076137,0.083311,0.089364,0.092056,0.096426,0.096541,0.094937,0.089811,0.087753,0.083998],"unified_progress":[0.043239,0.068987,0.07936,0.087686,0.093814,0.098131,0.097306,0.097223,0.096165,0.088477,0.079975,0.069636]},{"section":9,"text":"Another possibility could be a pineal gland tumor, but those are usually more posterior and might present with different symptoms.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030134,0.05357,0.06896,0.079979,0.090121,0.096412,0.104,0.10652,0.10559,0.10086,0.089376,0.074472],"unified_progress":[0.031775,0.059236,0.078512,0.089827,0.096275,0.10294,0.10279,0.10179,0.09961,0.096013,0.080057,0.061178]},{"section":10,"text":"Also, the presenc