CT scan reveals a suprasellar mass with calcification.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.076065,0.14218,0.13613,0.11628,0.096497,0.089317,0.077424,0.069259,0.069419,0.049906,0.042252,0.035268],"unified_progress":[0.065817,0.10729,0.11101,0.11538,0.11052,0.098307,0.088959,0.080086,0.083639,0.056343,0.045674,0.036967]},{"section":6,"text":"Hmm, first, the symptoms.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.071256,0.10831,0.11751,0.11358,0.10235,0.087328,0.081256,0.074466,0.066961,0.069948,0.054948,0.052083],"unified_progress":[0.10018,0.083792,0.089839,0.098325,0.096607,0.088445,0.089635,0.085202,0.077006,0.079794,0.061802,0.049369]},{"section":7,"text":"Headache is a common symptom for a brain mass, but the visual issues are key here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053866,0.10386,0.12395,0.12129,0.10579,0.088025,0.080899,0.073124,0.066174,0.07209,0.056416,0.054519],"unified_progress":[0.048858,0.082014,0.090101,0.10303,0.099533,0.095234,0.093762,0.089289,0.084415,0.088163,0.070276,0.055326]},{"section":8,"text":"The fact that he's missing the sides\u2014so that's a bitemporal hemianopia, right?","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.067548,0.1158,0.11065,0.10422,0.096211,0.091446,0.084219,0.079171,0.072893,0.06672,0.057794,0.053334],"unified_progress":[0.067315,0.092164,0.095053,0.10197,0.097344,0.09501,0.090769,0.088214,0.082007,0.07416,0.063029,0.052965]},{"section":9,"text":"Because the optic chiasm is where the nerves cross, so a mass there would typically cause that kind of visual field loss.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046493,0.092568,0.10238,0.10565,0.10213,0.097999,0.094048,0.085632,0.084507,0.072839,0.061773,0.053975],"unified_progress":[0.058278,0.078178,0.093724,0.10274,0.10426,0.10225,0.096507,0.090285,0.088684,0.074506,0.060674,0.049914]},{"section":10,"text":"But wait, the visual acuity is also